thread.title: Grain mostly higher, livestock mixed

title: Grain mostly higher, livestock mixed
text:
Sat, Aug 29, 2015, 12:55 AM AEST - Australia Markets closed Grain mostly higher, livestock mixed Grain mostly higher on the CBOT, beef higher and pork lower on the CME Associated Press – 22 minutes ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were mostly higher in early trading Friday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for December delivery lost 1.50 cents to $4.88 a bushel; December corn was 2.50 cents higher at $3.7760 a bushel; December oats were 1.50 cents higher at 2.2360 a bushel; while November soybeans gained 4.50 cents to 8.8340 a bushel. 
Beef higher and pork were lower on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. 
October live cattle was .23 cent higher at $1.4325 a pound; October feeder cattle was 1.85 cents higher at $1.9893 a pound; October lean hogs lost .40 cent to $.6665 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Blackmores' shares to carry on: Analyst AAP
